# 36 Views - CS50 SQL Problem Set

This project analyzes 72 woodblock prints from Hokusai and Hiroshige using SQL queries.

## Dataset
The dataset contains metadata about prints including:
- Titles (English & Japanese)
- Artist
- Brightness
- Contrast
- Entropy
- Average color

## Skills practiced
- SELECT queries
- Filtering with WHERE + LIKE
- Aggregation (COUNT, AVG, MAX)
- Sorting (ORDER BY)
- Limiting results (LIMIT)
- Column aliasing (AS)
- Rounding values (ROUND)

## Key Insights
- Hokusai and Hiroshige differ in visual brightness and contrast
- Statistical image properties can reflect artistic style

## Files
- 1.sql → Titles side-by-side
- 2.sql → River-themed prints (Hokusai)
- 3.sql → Fuji mentions count
- 4.sql → Eastern Capital references
- 5.sql → Maximum contrast
- 6.sql → Average entropy
- 7.sql → Brightest Hiroshige prints
- 8.sql → Least contrast Hokusai prints
- 9.sql → Brightest print overall
- 10.sql → Custom analysis
